keep the bishop.} ({The other possible line is} 6... Bxc3+ 7. Nxc3 d5 8. b3 O-O
9. Be2 Nc6 {White seems to have enough resources to defend c4, though:} 10. a4
dxc4 11. bxc4 Na5 12. Ba3 Re8 13. Nb5) 7. Ng3 {Just one of the possible ways
to defend c4.} (7. b3 d5 8. cxd5 (8. Ng3 {or}) (8. Nf4 {transpose to positions
examined below.}) 8... exd5 9. g3 O-O 10. Bg2 c6 {White's main problem is that
the usual minority's attack with b3-b4 would weaken the c4-square.} 11. O-O
Nbd7 12. Re1 Re8 13. Nf4 Bd6 14. Bb2 Re7 (14... Qe7 $1 {is more natural and
