13. exd4 Nxd4 14. Nxe7+ Qxe7 15. Bg5 Qe5 16. Bxf6 Qxf6 17. Nd5 Qd6 18. Bxh7+
Kxh7 19. Qxd4 c6 20. Qh4+ Qh6 21. Qxh6+ Kxh6 22. Ne3 f5 $11) 9... c6 {Not the
only good plan. Black intends to prepare ...e6-e5.} (9... Bd6 $5 10. Bd3 (10.
Qf3 {Akobian,V (2547)-Burnett,R (2442) Stratton Mountain 2003 (1-0, 34)} c6 {
transposes to a familiar position.}) 10... dxc4 (10... Bxf4 11. exf4 Nc6 12.
Ne2 $1 $14) 11. bxc4 e5 $5 (11... Nc6 12. c5 $1 $14) 12. dxe5 Bxe5 13. O-O Nbd7
14. Qc2 Nc5 15. Be2 c6 $13) (9... dxc4 10. Bxc4 {This gains a tempo compared
to the line starting with 9.Be2 above. But Black nevertheless has good play} (
10. bxc4 $6 Nc6) 10... Bxc4 11. bxc4 Nc6 12. O-O Na5 13. Qd3 Bd6 14. Rfd1 Qd7
15. Rac1 Nb3 16. Rc2 Nxd4 $1 17. Qxd4 e5 {Black is not worse.}) 10. Be2 (10.
Bd3 Bd6 11. O-O Nbd7 12. Rc1 (12. Nh5 Nxh5 13. Qxh5 f5 {A good moment to
transpose to a Stonewall structure, as White's knight is far from e5.} 14. Qe2
Rc8 15. f3 Qh4 16. g3 Qh3 17. Rad1 {Botvinnik,M-Novotelnov,N Moscow 1951 27
septembrie 2003 [Bob,Doru] (1-0, 87)} Nf6 $11) 12... Rc8 13. Nh5 Nxh5 14. Qxh5
f5 {The same idea as above.} 15. Qe2 Qh4 16. g3 Qh3 17. f3 Rce8 18. Rc2 Bb7 19.
Qg2 Qh6 20. Qd2 c5 $11 {Black is perfectly regrouped and his structure is not
worse, Akobian,V (2601)-Friedel,J (2484) Las Vegas 2008 (0-1, 63)}) 10... Nbd7
11. O-O Bd6 12. Re1 Re8 $1 $146 {It is a good idea to make all the useful
moves before undertaking any specific actions in the centre.} (12... dxc4 13.
bxc4 e5 {is slightly premature.} 14. Nh3 exd4 (14... Re8 {is not effective due
to} 15. Ng5 $1) (14... h6 {looks entirely playable, though.}) 15. exd4 Qb8 16.
g3 $14 {Gorman,D (2241)-Krush,I (2475) ICC INT 2015 (0-1, 58)}) 13. Qc2 (13.
Nh3 {does not force Black to transpose to a line above. He is flexible enough
to change plans:} dxc4 14. bxc4 c5 15. Ng5 Qc7 16. Nf3 e5 17. d5 e4 {with
excellent play.}) 13... dxc4 14. bxc4 e5 15. Nh3 h6 $11 {With the white knight
all the way back on h3, Black has comfortable play.} *

