O-O 9. Be3 {Prior to castling, White definitely needs to cover the e-file up.}
(9. O-O {allows} Bxc3 10. bxc3 exd5 11. exd5 Bf5 $1 12. Qxf5 {Otherwise Black
has very active play.} (12. Qd1 Ne4 13. Re1 Qf6) (12. Qd2 Nbd7 {leaves White
with a rather ugly position.}) (12. Qb2 Nbd7 13. Re1 Ne5 14. Bg5 Rfe8 15. Qd2 {
