{gives away the d5-square for nothing.} Nd5 13. Qxa8 (13. Qb5 {is pointless.}
O-O 14. Nf3 Qb6 15. Qxd3 {1-0 (54) Lee,J (2238)-Omar,N (2377) Baku 2016} h6 16.
O-O Nc6 $17 {White has a very passive bishop.}) 13... Qc7 {Preventing Qb7 and
threatening ...0-0 followed by ...Qc3.} 14. Rb1 Nb6 15. Qe4 (15. Rxb6 Qxc1#)
15... Qc2 16. Nf3 Qxb1 17. O-O Qc2 18. Qg4 Kf8 19. Bd2 Nc6 20. Rc1 Qa4 $17)
12... Qb6 13. Ra2 $1 $146 {The only move that keeps White in the game.} (13.
Nf3 $2 O-O 14. Be3 Na6 15. Qxf8+ Kxf8 16. O-O Nxe4 $19 {Lysyj,I (2671)
-Morozevich,A (2711) Poikovsky 2015 (0-1, 31)}) 13... O-O ({ANother possible
line is} 13... Qb1 14. Ra1 Qb6 {With a draw by repetition.}) 14. Rb2 $1 {
