Ne2 Ra4 20. Bb2 Na5 $5 $17) 15... Qxd4+ 16. Ke1 {White is best adviced to take
a draw by perpetual.} (16. Ke2 $2 Qc4+ 17. Kd1 (17. Kd2 Nxe4+) 17... Nc6 18.
Qb7 Qf1+ 19. Kc2 Qxg2 $19) 16... Qc3+ 17. Kd1 Qd4+ 18. Rd2 $6 Qa4+ 19. Ke1 Nxe4
20. Qb7 Nxd2 21. Bxd2 Nc6 {with a dangerous attack for the piece, as the enemy
